8 AI Prompts Websites You Will Love

neoBazinga
3 min read
·
Mar 23, 2024

Do you ever get the sense that crafting AI prompts demands some sort of arcane knowledge or mystical skill? How do all these imaginative professionals manage to conjure up such breathtaking, mind-bending visuals using tools like Midjourney and DALL-E, while your own prompts seem to lack that spark? Well, the truth is, creating impressive AI prompts isn’t as daunting as it may appear. With the right tools (websites), you can leverage simple keywords and formulas to churn out top-notch AI prompts.

I’m sure you already know how AI generation works!, it’s time to start crafting your prompts. Here are a few websites you can use when writing good AI prompts.

Table of contents

  • Learning Prompt
  • Prompt flow
  • LangChain Hub
  • PromptPort
  • PromptKnit
  • ChatGPT Shortcut
  • Prompt Extend
  • PromptPerfect

Very detailed Prompt learning resources, including ChatGPT and MidJourney

learningprompt.wiki

2. Prompt flow

Microsoft released Prompt flow, an open source LLM development toolset that simplifies the end-to-end development cycle for LLM-based AI applications, from ideation, prototyping, testing, and evaluation to production deployment and monitoring, and is useful for simple workflows.

Prompt flow - Prompt flow documentation

Prompt flow Doc

microsoft.github.io
